Items.description: Danny Jansen hit a go-ahead, three-run homer, George Springer also went deep and the Blue Jays beat the Minnesota Twins 5-2 Sunday to maintain pressure in the AL wild-card race before heading to Toronto for their final homestand.
Items.vs: Minnesota Twins vs. Toronto Blue Jays

Items.description: Andrew Knizner slid across home plate, hopped up and pumped his right arm in jubilation.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: The San Francisco Giants moved closer to a division title with a clutch win. Now they hope their home run leader can be help them capture the crown.

Items.description: Shohei Ohtani wasn't enough to keep the Los Angeles Angeles from their sixth straight losing season.

Items.description: Mark Canha hit an RBI single with one out in the bottom of the ninth inning and the Oakland Athletics again beat Houston with their final swing, edging the AL West-leading Astros 4-3 Sunday.

Items.description: The dominant Dodgers rolled to win No. 100 of the season on Sunday afternoon with a mix that's served them well all season: terrific starting pitching, a few long homers and a shutdown bullpen.
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Will Smith struck out the side around three walks in the ninth inning to finish the Atlanta Braves' 4-3 win over the San Diego Padres on Sunday that opened a 2 1/2-game lead over Philadelphia heading into their NL East showdown.

Items.description: Yankees manager Aaron Boone watched two of his Gold Glove fielders drop easy popups to hand the Red Sox the lead.

Items.description: As they've done in countless ninth innings over decades, fans in Progressive Field stood to cheer during the final three outs.

Items.description: Josiah Gray pitched into the sixth inning to earn his second career win, and the Washington Nationals beat the Colorado Rockies 5-4 on Monday night.

Items.description: After two years away, Noah Syndergaard was still nasty.

Items.description: Now comes the changing to the Guardians for the Cleveland baseball team that played 107 seasons as the Indians.
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. Cleveland Indians
